            <h3 style="color: coral"> What you need to know about car rentals</h3>
            <p>Need to rent a car for your next vacation? Before booking, take a look at our commonly asked questions below:</p>
            <h1> </h1>
            <h3 style="color: coral">How to get a cheap rent car?</h3>
            <p>The best way to make savings on a rental vehicle is to:</p>
            <ol>
                <li>Compare lots of different cheap car rental rates!</li>
                <li>Prepay for your rental and get some of the cheapest rates.</li>
                <li>Check for the latest deals.</li>
                <li>
                    Set a price drop alert and get an email when prices are low for your location.
                    Don’t get an airport car rental since airport locations have higher prices. An off-airport drop-off rental location will also help you to make big savings.
                </li>
                <li>Know what you need (how much fuel and mileage you’ll use and the required size of the car).</li>
                <li>Book in advance, as soon as you know what you need. No credit card needed—you simply pay at pickup.</li>
            </ol>
            <h1> </h1>
            <h3 style="color: coral">Are there car rental locations that accept debit cards?</h3>
            <p>
                Yes, some companies accept debit cards on upcoming reservations, though they will usually require additional identification and proof of insurance.
                They may also need to run a credit check. Cash, pre-paid cards, and gift cards are never accepted for any reservation type.
            </p>
            <h1> </h1>
            <h3 style="color: coral">Do I need insurance for renting a car?</h3>
            <p>
                Yes. You will need to be insured in order to drive car rentals. Firstly, you should check if your car insurance or your credit card covers your car for rent. If it doesn’t, you can always book one with the rental car company – just be careful to check what it covers! As a U.S. Citizen, you also have the option to purchase
                insurance with CarRentals.com at check out, since it isn't usually included in rental rates. When renting in some countries,
                such as Mexico, you have to buy an additional local insurance.
            </p>
            <h1> </h1>
            <h3 style="color: coral">How old do I have to be to rent a car?</h3>
            <p>
                You usually must be between 25 and 65 years of age for renting cars. This can vary depending on the location. You might still be able
                to get cheap car rentals if you’re outside of this age range, but be prepared to pay an additional fee or purchase additional insurance.
            </p>
            <h1> </h1>
            <h3 style="color: coral">What car is the most suiting one for me?</h3>
            <p>
                This is entirely up to you and your trip – factor in things
                like your budget and how many people you will be driving with. Here are some suggestions to get you started:
            </p>
            <h1> </h1>
            <table class="table table-bordered">
                <tr>
                    <th>Car Type</th>
                    <th>Best for </th>
                    <th>Category includes</th>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td><b>Economy car</b></td>
                    <td>Lower costs and smaller groups</td>
                    <td>Toyota Yaris, Vauxhall Corsa, or similar</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td><b>SUV</b></td>
                    <td>Longer day trips with more people</td>
                    <td>Audi Q7, Ford Escape, or similar</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td><b>Luxury</b></td>
                    <td>Romantic couples seeking a memorable getaway</td>
                    <td>Chrysler 300, Buick Lacrosse, or similar</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td><b>Full-size SUV</b></td>
                    <td>Larger groups needing comfort and luggage space</td>
                    <td>Ford Edge, KIA Sorento, or similar</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td><b>Convertible</b></td>
                    <td>Sightseers wanting to soak up the weather and scenery</td>
                    <td>Chevy Camaro, VW Beetle Convertible, or similar</td>
